entries.femaleVariant: Yes?
V, what's shakin'?
Mr. Hands? Name's V. Heard you're the one to see about any and all work in Pacifica.
Nice opening. Flattered me right out of the gate, I'm sold.
How is it I can help you?
Need to make contact with the Voodoo Boys' chief, if you can swing it.
Need to make contact with the Voodoo Boys' chief, if you can swing it.
All right, all right, straight to heavy business.
All right, all right, straight to heavy business.
Hmm... Now, that'd be Maman Brigitte. Be tough gettin' a word in to her.
Don't do any biz with them?
Thought you could arrange anything.
Uh, I was led to believe you could arrange anything.
entries.maleVariant: Huh, I was led to believe you could arrange anything.

entries.femaleVariant: Hah! Now that sounded like my third wife every time she wanted a new purse.
Really don't do any biz with 'em?
entries.maleVariant: You really don't do any biz with 'em?

entries.femaleVariant: Not with the chefs, chefins, priests and whatnot. All got dirigible-sized egos, won't talk to lowly me.
But if you insist, I can ask around, try to set somethin' up. I'll just need some details first.
Nope, sorry, it's personal.
Got something they want.
Sorry, it's personal.
Well, that's fucking helpful.
Ahh, got something they want.
Truly? Wanna sell somethin' to the VDBs? Trust me, they don't want it, they don't need it.
They're isolated, insulated, got their own contracts, tech, networks... But have it your way.
Gimme a sec.
V? V! Consider this your lucky day – if you hear Pacifica callin' you to make sweet love to it, that is.
Got somethin' for me?
Well, it's like I said – whatever you're peddlin', the VDBS're just not in the market.
But they have another task that needs doin', so I volunteered you. Do it well, and you'll get your audience with Brigitte.
What's the job?
OK, so who do I talk to?
What's this task needs doin'?
OK, so who do I talk to and how?
What, you gonna go picky on me, now?
The contact'll fill you in on the detes.
I got zero from 'im. Actually, got the impression I'd have to pay for every word out of his mouth.
Hit the chapel on Sloane, look for the altar inside. Someone'll touch you, nod to you – somethin' spooky.
Got it. Thanks.
Hm, claims zero contacts with the Voodoos but seems pretty damn sure his call won't get ghosted.
OK, I'll see what I can do and get back to ya.
V? V! Consider this your lucky day – if you hear Pacifica callin' you to make sweet love to it, that is.
Got somethin' for me?
Well, it's like I said – whatever you're peddlin', the "VD-BS" are just not in the market.
But they have another task that needs doin', so I volunteered you. Do it well and you'll get your audience with Brigitte.
"Maman Brigitte"? That a nickname, a cover?
"Maman Brigitte." Now that sounds like a spooky cult alias.
Have not had the pleasure of asking her personally.
But it is what everybody calls her. Doubt the title has any real religious weight, though.
Voodoo Boys play pretty fast and loose with their Haitian heritage.
One and only fixer in Pacifica.
They can't afford to blacklist him completely.
